revisions.description: The initial version of this MIB module.

EnabledStatus.name: EnabledStatus
EnabledStatus.description: The current state of the Ethernet port. This object has two defined values: - 'enabled', which indicates that the Ethernet port enables DLDP. - 'disabled', which indicates that the Ethernet port does not enable DLDP.

DLDPStatus.name: DLDPStatus
DLDPStatus.description: Operating state of DLDP on the port. This object has six defined values: - 'initial', which indicates that the Ethernet port does not enable DLDP. This status does not appear in the 'hpnicfDLDPPortDLDPState' object (below) because the port which is not enabled DLDP does not appear in 'hpnicfDLDPPortDLDPTable', it appears in 'hpnicfDLDPPortStateTable'. - 'inactive', which indicates that the Ethernet port enables DLDP and the link status of the port is down. - 'active', which indicates that the Ethernet port enables DLDP and the link status of the port is up. - 'advertisement', which indicates that all neighbors of the port are bidirectional communication. - 'probe', which indicates that the port sends PDU to detect the communication mode between it and it's neighbors. - 'disable', which indicates that an unidirectional communication between the port and it's neighbor. When the user get or walk the 'hpnicfDLDPPortDLDPState' objects (below) these status will output.

DLDPNeighborStatus.name: DLDPNeighborStatus
DLDPNeighborStatus.description: The current state of the neighbor of a port. This object has three defined values: - 'unidirection', which indicates an unidirectional communication between the port and it's neighbor. - 'bidirection', which indicates a bidirectional communication between the port and it's neighbor. - 'unknown', which indicates that the port does not know the communication mode between it and it's neighbor. When the user get or walk the 'hpnicfDLDPNeighborState' objects (below) these status will output.

hpnicfDLDPWorkMode.name: hpnicfDLDPWorkMode
hpnicfDLDPWorkMode.description: The work mode of DLDP. Normal mode means DLDP does not detect neighbor on its own initiative when all neighbors aged. Enhance mode means DLDP detects neighbor on its own initiative when all neighbors aged.

hpnicfDLDPSystemEnable.name: hpnicfDLDPSystemEnable
hpnicfDLDPSystemEnable.description: DLDP enable or disable systematically. This node only supports set operation. If setting it to true, all the fiber ports will enable DLDP and the agent automatically creates new rows for each port in hpnicfDLDPPortDLDPTable. If setting it to false, all the fiber ports will disable DLDP and the agent automatically destroy the corresponding rows in hpnicfDLDPPortDLDPTable.

hpnicfDLDPSystemReset.name: hpnicfDLDPSystemReset
hpnicfDLDPSystemReset.description: DLDP reset systematically. This node only supports set operation. If the value of hpnicfDLDPSystemReset is true, and the current state is disable, it will change to inactive while the port is down or active while the port is up. If hpnicfDLDPPortDLDPState is not disable, it does not change.

hpnicfDLDPInterval.name: hpnicfDLDPInterval
hpnicfDLDPInterval.description: The interval of sending an advertisement PDU. unit : second

hpnicfDLDPAuthenticationPassword.name: hpnicfDLDPAuthenticationPassword
hpnicfDLDPAuthenticationPassword.description: This is the password for authentication. If the value of hpnicfDLDPAuthenticationMode is null, the user cannot set this node. If the value of hpnicfDLDPAuthenticationMode is simple or MD5, the user must set this node with a string. When the user gets or walks this node, it displays a cipher password if hpnicfDLDPAuthenticationMode is MD5 or simple or a zero-length string if hpnicfDLDPAuthenticationMode is null.

hpnicfDLDPUnidirectionalShutdown.name: hpnicfDLDPUnidirectionalShutdown
hpnicfDLDPUnidirectionalShutdown.description: The mode of unidirectional shutdown. It indicates the shutdown mode when a unidirectional link happened. Auto mode means the port will be shut down automatically when DLDP detects unidirectional link. Manual mode means the port needs to be shut down by the administrator manually when DLDP detects unidirectional link.

hpnicfDLDPPortStateTable.name: hpnicfDLDPPortStateTable
hpnicfDLDPPortStateTable.description: The table of the Ethernet ports of a LAN switch.

hpnicfDLDPPortState.name: hpnicfDLDPPortState
hpnicfDLDPPortState.description: State of a port. If setting it to enabled, the port will enable DLDP and a new row will be added in hpnicfDLDPPortDLDPTable for this port. If setting it to disabled, the port will disable DLDP and the corresponding row will be destroyed in hpnicfDLDPPortDLDPTable.

hpnicfDLDPPortDLDPTable.name: hpnicfDLDPPortDLDPTable
hpnicfDLDPPortDLDPTable.description: Table of a LAN switch's ports, which enable DLDP.

hpnicfDLDPPortDLDPEntry.name: hpnicfDLDPPortDLDPEntry
hpnicfDLDPPortDLDPEntry.description: The information of a port, which enable DLDP.

hpnicfDLDPPortDLDPState.name: hpnicfDLDPPortDLDPState
hpnicfDLDPPortDLDPState.description: Operating state of DLDP on the port. It is relational with hpnicfDLDPPortState and hpnicfDLDPLinkState.

hpnicfDLDPLinkState.name: hpnicfDLDPLinkState
hpnicfDLDPLinkState.description: The link state of the port.

hpnicfDLDPPortDLDPReset.name: hpnicfDLDPPortDLDPReset
hpnicfDLDPPortDLDPReset.description: DLDP reset systematically. This node only supports set operation. If the value of hpnicfDLDPPortDLDPReset is true, and the current state is disable, it will change to inactive while the port is down or active while the port is up.

hpnicfDLDPNeighborBridgeMac.name: hpnicfDLDPNeighborBridgeMac
hpnicfDLDPNeighborBridgeMac.description: The bridge MAC address of a neighbor.

hpnicfDLDPNeighborPortIndex.name: hpnicfDLDPNeighborPortIndex
hpnicfDLDPNeighborPortIndex.description: The port index of a neighbor.

hpnicfDLDPNeighborAgingTime.name: hpnicfDLDPNeighborAgingTime
hpnicfDLDPNeighborAgingTime.description: The aging time of a neighbor. unit: second.

hpnicfDLDPUnidirectionalPort.name: hpnicfDLDPUnidirectionalPort
hpnicfDLDPUnidirectionalPort.description: It will send a SNMP trap when the state of a port has changed to unidirectional-link.
